The E.C. President refused to comment on the current situation in Portugal, but admitted to have been "surprised"  by the Portuguese President's decision to call for new elections, ending the government's term a full year early.
Barroso was the former Prime Minister of the current Portuguese government and leader of the ruling PSD party.
He stepped down to accept the nomination for President of the European Commission, favouring current Prime-Minister Pedro Santana Lopes as his successor.
