After midnight Castro communicated by telephone with Uribe for two hours.
They decided that Castro would send his Vice-chancellor with a letter detailing what they had talked about to Chávez.
During the World Social Forum in Porto Alegre Chavez appeared to be optimistic about the end of the crisis.
