At that time it was Boutros Boutros-Ghali who was the Secretary-General.
And the report asserts that he tried to please the Saddam government by accommodating its requests which laid the basis for most things that went wrong later....
What's clear to me is that Saddam and his regime were able to manipulate things in such a way as to get what they wanted out of this program."
