ARTICLE 4152
FARC attack: 16 Colombian soldiers dead
February 2, 2005 
ISCUANDÉ, Colombia
The Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia-FARC attacked Colombian navy soldiers at the city of Iscuandé, Nariño in Colombia.
16 soldiers from the navy died in the attack and 25 were injured.
The attack started at 02:40 and finished at 05:20 yesterday February 1st.
